00:26:34.538 --> 00:26:37.778
established selection biomarker, and so we don't want to override that.

458
00:26:37.858 --> 00:26:41.338
We think there could be potential for GIS to help distinguish

459
00:26:41.858 --> 00:26:45.218
better responders within BRCA. That doesn't always have a particularly high

460
00:26:45.278 --> 00:26:47.758
response rate, depending on the indication and the drug.

461
00:26:48.718 --> 00:26:52.638
But that is still out for debate and requires a

462
00:26:52.678 --> 00:26:56.398
lot of future validation data to show that type of

463
00:26:56.458 --> 00:26:57.938
application. So,

464
00:26:58.778 --> 00:27:02.578
in the near future, we see it as a complement to

465
00:27:02.698 --> 00:27:03.818
HR gene profiling.

466
00:27:04.758 --> 00:27:08.438
Guardant360 tissue also has methylation profiling, so we think

