00:27:35.858 --> 00:27:37.798
developed, also sequencing-based,

474
00:27:38.678 --> 00:27:42.478
for the signature and the advantages of the assay that you've been

475
00:27:42.558 --> 00:27:44.278
using compared to others?

476
00:27:45.378 --> 00:27:48.238
Yeah. So Guardant360 tissue is a relatively new

477
00:27:48.918 --> 00:27:49.458
platform.

478
00:27:50.448 --> 00:27:54.218
And so we haven't had a chance to compare it to orthogonal assays yet.

479
00:27:54.238 --> 00:27:58.218
But I think one major advantage we have is that it's a relatively large

480
00:27:58.298 --> 00:28:01.858
gene panel. We have full coverage of BRCA1 and 2.

